annotation.TEXT: Aha, more doors up here!
Well, the shell did allow me to hit that switch, but I don't know if that was important or not.
And, I think that was just a single coin block, not the "multi" variety.
Yep, looks like the springboard is needed here.
BGM: Asterix and Obelix - The Mountains
Push!
Not sure what the springboard there was meant for.
No, there's no way he'd be trapped forever. You're a liar. A liar! Liar, liar, pants on fire!
A 4th midpoint? But, I'm at the 15m mark now. Well, maybe I'm 4/5 done at this point. I mean, I did spend a few minutes on non-required things, such as that bonus room.
MOON!!!
This brown block wall has a gap in it, not that I'm complaining.
Alright, I guess I won! (The 1-up was from my 0 stars matching the 0 timer, and the drumroll was from the 0 x 50 = 0 time bonus being added to my non-existent score.)
Well, I can reach this P-switch now.
BGM: Donkey Kong Country 2 - Haunted Chase
Lucky landing on that guy there.
BGM: SMB3 (All-Stars) - P-switch
Another door. So, which way should I go? Well, the game's probably expecting me to go right, so... I'm going to defy its expectations and go left!
Oh, right! You can stand on these clocks! And, I'd been landing on clocks earlier, so I really should've seen that right away. Well, at that brain fart didn't cost me much time.
Why is everything all dark and dreary again?
There's a power up, but nothing to use the P-switch on, and no springboard in sight? ...Hmm... I'm thinking hidden P-switch ? blocks are present in this room now.
So, remember when I did a playthrough of The Haunted Desert two years ago? Well, I was just requested a few days ago to play this REMASTERED version!
I hope I chose correctly... Oh, geez. Even that Boo has gone blind. The kerneling process must be really horrific in this Deported Temple, so I'd better find Luigi fast!
Oh, I think I remember this room from the original Haunted Desert. So, there should be a P-switch to the right, right?
See, I just found a P-switch silhouette.
Also, my reserve mushroom was flickering as I was bouncing off of Chuck there. Sprite memory issue, perhaps?
Whoa, what? I saw a cape feather for a split-second there. Oh, whoa!
Let's make sure the ON/OFF switches are set correctly as I go!
And then I take a dumb hit while trying to retrieve this shell that I probably don't need.
Well, that was pointless, but I was hoping for another power up to be along that one-way path.
Another locked door... Hmm... Which one should I enter? Well, in the original Haunted Desert, I think the P-switch door was on the right side, so I'll pick this one.
Oh, a flower! Me wantee!
DOUBLE KILL!
Oh, I'm suddenly going back through this room, only there's no auto-scroll, no Magikoopa, and no shell-kickers to auto-activate these ON/OFF blocks.
Huh. I could go in that door right there, but... I can also continue left from here...
D'oh! I can blame my hastiness on that one. Why am I being so hasty anyway? Didn't I just mention how there's no time limit?
Umm... Oh.
Actually, it's a key. Huh.
I think I remember the original Haunted Desert having a number of reset doors, so maybe that was one as well.
The bullet cannons seem to all be non-functional now.
A Thwimp?
And, there's the P-switch. I could've saved some time if I had just gone left at first when I entered this room, but I didn't, so... kerneled corn.
What, another midpoint? Okay, so this is one of those multiple-midpoint levels. That explains how the first midpoint came so early. So, this might be the actual 50% mark.
BLOCK FACTORYYY!!! Okay, enough of that.
Oh, it's Luigi! He hasn't actually been kerneled yet! I knew it! ...Also, you can't stand on or in the cage.
Oh, Luigi! ...You okay, buddy? They didn't kernel you, did they?
Maybe that's why everyone here is blind, because of how horrific the tedium of kerneling has been. Anyway, there's a P-switch over there.
...Huh? No hidden blocks or anything? So, did I need to bring the springboard here somehow? ...But... How do I do that?
Alright, here's some Koopduders... Wait, do they not have eyes? Oh, no... Did they witness someone getting kerneled and go blind from the horror?
...Ahem... Sorry, I mean... Welcome to... The Haunted Desert: REMASTERED!
Push!
Okay, so we have a pipe here that I'll need a P-switch for.
There's a locked door, but what's to the right?
I'm gonna go with Deported, since this temple totally looks like it came from another country to me.
Yet another 1-up that I don't need.
Maybe those are the doors I need to enter, but I do see that rope to the upper-left...
Oh, there was text down there that I didn't show very well. I went back and checked, and it says, "It's too late". Okay, so let's go into this door over here...
I'm not trapped. You're lying. If I was really trapped, then I'd be ending the video here, but seeing how there's still 9 min. left of the video, I'm clearly able to get out of here.
Somehow, I managed to avoid getting hurt by that Chuck.
Oh, come on. That was cheap. I had no idea there would be spikes right there, and I didn't even hit the sharp points. Darn SMW engine making spikes hurt on all sides...
Oh, I'm gonna need the assistance of Mr. Bones here to get up to the next ledge.
DOUBLE KILL!
Luigi... kneed? ...Knifed? ...Kerneled? Oh, god... I really hope he wasn't kerneled...
I could go for some kerneled corn about now.
BGM: Zelda: A Link to the Past - Dark World Dungeon
There sure are a lot of skeletal enemies around here now.
Alright, let's head to The Haunted Desert and find Luigi, hopefully before he's kerneled!
Yay, Luigi wasn't kerneled after all!
Actually, I can't run out of time, since there's no time limit in this level.
Okay, this is the end of the line, and there was not really much for me to use this P-switch on, so I'll get 3 extra coins with it, I guess.
BGM: SMB1 (All-Stars) - Course Clear
Oh, that glitch works, where I can carry a stomped P-switch through the pipe and have it come back brand new on the other side.
This sounds like a bonus room, and it looks like a bonus room too. I bet it also smells like a bonus room. However, it probably tastes like chicken.
Oh, but now we have auto-scrolling, and floating magic.
BGM: Zelda: A Link to the Past - Turned Into a Rabbit
BGM: Silent Hill - Alternate Hospital Basement
Cheap! I call shenanigans on that one! Man, I've taken 3 hits in quick succession here, and I think only one of them was entirely my fault.
Happy Halloween! And welcome to...
...Desired Temple? ...Deported? ...Derriered? ...Well, it can't be Deserted because there are duders dwelling here, even if they're blind.
Umm... Yeah, nuts to that 1-up. I'd have to be small to reach it. Totally not worth it.
Add a period here.
Whoa! Somehow I didn't get hurt there!
The flower and mushroom power ups don't have eyes either, and neither does Chuck. This is a bad omen...
Whoops, that was an accidental double-grab. Also, no key here? Well, I bet I'll need the springboard to find the key elsewhere in the room.
Alright, so that's what we're doing here. And, while we're doing this, a Magikoopa is gonna be harassing me. I bet all these turn blocks are just here for Magikoopa to use.
Heh, it's a coin shape made out of coins.
Not that saving/wasting time is important, because I don't see any time limit here. (Still, I wouldn't want to waste too much time and make the video unnecessarily long.)
Oh, and I guess that's it. So, let's watch the credits roll. And, I hope you all enjoyed watching me play through The Haunted Desert: REMASTERED! See y'all later!
That would be a far worse fate than merely being kidnapped.
Okay, there's a P-switch up there.
And I hope you trick-or-treaters out there got lots of delicious non-tainted candy!
BLOCK FACTORYYY!!!
And that right there was me just being sloppy.
Never give up! Never surrender!
Oh, I'm sure he's in The Haunted Desert level.
Man, even the fish have gone blind. Is the kerneling process being done in or near water?
Gotcha! Okay, let's see if I can avoid losing this power up.
Aha, and there it is, along with more ceiling spikes that I'll want to carefully avoid hitting.
There's a door, but I don't need the springboard for it. Let's go to a location that requires the springboard, like further up.
BGM: SMB1 and The Lost Levels (All-Stars) - Bonus Room
I like being able to hit two side-by-side ? blocks at once like that if I aim properly.
Okay, so I got a 1-up and two mushrooms, but now which double-door do I enter? Or, does it even matter?
And, there was a locked door up there. Seems like I'll need to find a springboard in order to reach it.
Yep, there's the P-switch blocks. Also, there's a repeating sound effect added to the P-switch music.
My reserve mushroom sure flickers a lot while I'm stomping and kicking stuff. I wonder if it was made to do that intentionally?
And, all that for a 1-up. Okay, whatever.
NO!!! Don't tell me you've kerneled him already! ...No, I don't believe you! I DON'T LISTEN!!!
There's a door to the left, but what's to the right?
Oh, dear... I seem to be in a more dreary version of a familiar room...
The springboard will make getting back to the locked door easier, so I'll go back for it.
P-switch jumps: 1
Okay, there's a door in the upper-right, but what's further to the left?
Okay, I'm leaving the shell behind here, in favor of the springboard. I could try to double-grab, but I'm sure it's not worth it.
BGM: SMB3 (All-Stars) - Ending
Okay, I'm outside again, and... let's see if I can block clone a power up block here, to make up for the cheapness I experienced in the previous room.
Nuts, my shell isn't in a proper sprite slot to kill it.
Okay, so I saw a locked door and a key that requires a P-switch to reach...
Okay, so both of those double doors take me to the same place. Now, let's go down to the other set of double doors below.
Now, I don't know if this hack has that fix to prevent a better reserve item from being overwritten by a mushroom, but I'm not gonna risk it.
Oh, dude! It's a rampagin' star! Let's go rampagin'!
Zwee! Now, the SMW Central description of this hack says that it takes about 15 minutes to beat without dying, but I've already hit midpoint only about 3 minutes in?
Okay, this room gives me a springboard to start off with.
Those Boo Blocks have an eerie green outline while they're in Boo form.
Master combo! (7 hits, 0 points, because this hack doesn't have points.)
Oh, what? Oh, it's a bridge-building segment. There better not be too many of these, since they quickly get as tedious as the kerneling process.
Also, getting hit while fiery only took me to my regular super state, without instantly shrinking me, so that's cool to know.
Can't reenter that pipe, and this room seems to lack reset doors, so I think the player could get trapped by squandering the P-switch before reaching the pipe on the right.
Uh, oh! I can't reach that door! Is there any other exit around here?
Whoa, I gotta be careful of those ceiling spikes.
Oh, maybe hitting that switch with the shell earlier was important! (Or, maybe I just skipped a puzzle in an unintended way by doing that.)
Ow, stupid ceiling spikes that I totally did see. I haven't gone blind from witnessing the kerneling process yet!
Oh, so this block actually had a key. I don't know why I thought I saw a feather at first. Well, let's get outta here!
That sound effect even speeds up as the P-switch effect is close to running out. That's kinda neat.
You're welcome!
Whoa, whoops!
Looks like I've got a choice of paths here. Well, let's take the path that isn't one-way.
There's another door I could enter, but I can also keep going down.
And... here's a locked door, but there's no key...? Oh, is the key found in that one-way path below?
D'oh! I was trying to avoid letting that happen!
And, there's the P-switch.
Yep, there it is.
None of those were even power up blocks, unfortunately.
Well, that could've been worse. Still, I must be more careful.
Huh. Pressing start on the title screen took me straight to the world map, without even interrupting the music. Okay, so there are two levels I can play here.
Uh, oh. It was a load-bearing boss! ...Wait, I didn't even battle a boss. Well, it was a load-bearing something!
Oh, I could've gone down on this side to avoid having to blindly do a "science" on the right. Well, at least I didn't end up dying and messing with the space-time continuum.
That's a tricky 5-tile jump with little running room to use.
Well, that door led me back out here, but I can just go back in, right?
Obviously, I'll be starting with The Story Begins.
And now I'm in a submerged area with more blind fish.
Oh, I should've checked to see if the above bonus room was accessible again, for possibly more power ups. Oh, well.
D'oh! That was me being sloppy again.
Uhh... Okay, it's dark, but I can clearly still shoot fireballs... Umm...
There's a 1-up up there, but I'm not really concerned about that.
Okay, there's a door that requires a P-switch.
Okay, so I can go left or right here. Hmm...
That is a really tight jump to reach the P-switch.
Huh, it didn't make its usual sound effect (likely due to the other sounds playing here), but it was correctly added to my lives.
Oh, a pipe.
I wish I had left more enemies alive back here now.
Umm... Is there anything down below? I feel like doing a "science".
Quite a bit more stuff, so that door had to have been the wrong one.
I guess this is where I need the springboard.
Whoa! That bullet cannon is fully operational!
P-switch jumps: 2
Fortunately, no Boo Ring here now, although there are some Boo Blocks.
Random Bob-omb. Sure, why not?
Okay, things appear to be back to normal now...
I saw a locked door surrounded by brown blocks up there, along with a springboard.
Oh, and there's a key, which I'm sure I'll need.
Just another 1-up there. I was hoping for a power up.
Oh, I can move to the right, and that makes text scroll onto the screen. Well, I would be less lost if you turned on the lights for me... Oh, what?!
Well, I can't get the 1-up again, but I can grab more power ups, and I'm perfectly fine with this little bit of power up farming, after the shenanigans of that earlier room.
Ah, there is! I bet I'll need that springboard above.
And, I can apparently shoot and move around behind the scenes. So, what do I do? Move to the right, maybe?
Ooh, a 1-up. It's pointless, but I'm sure that I'm not really on a time limit, so why not?
A third midpoint, at the 12:34.5 mark in the video, interestingly enough. I guess I can assume I'm 3/4 done with the level now, since the expected clear time is about 15m.
Well, here's the P-switch, next to a door behind a brown block wall, but that's too obvious, so I think I want to actually go get the key and go through that locked door.
Whoa! I didn't expect that!
